n                      \n                     \n                        namo$iY EalaY Aln~amaAriqi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "We are the daughters of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "one like"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a star,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a morning-star: we bend not to a lover: we walk upon the pillows"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, * O, * TA:) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "we are the daughters of a chief;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "likening him to the star in elevation; (O, TA;) i. e. our father is, in respect of elevation, like the shining star: (S:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAtu TaAriqK", "text_ar": "بَنَاتُ طَارِقٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The daughters of the kings."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bnY", "text_ar": "بنى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaAriqN", "text_ar": "طَارِقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A diviner:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and particularly,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by means of pebbles; a practiser of pessomancy:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or] one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who is nearly a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAhin", "text_ar": "كَاهِن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "possessing more knowledge than such as is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAzK", "text_ar": "حَازٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (ISh, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HzY", "text_ar": "حزى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tur~aAqN", "text_ar": "طُرَّاقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[is its p., and] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "practisers of divination:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TawaAriqu", "text_ar": "طَوَارِقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaAriqapN", "text_ar": "طَارِقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and thus] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "female practisers of divination:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Lebeed says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "laEamoruka maA tadoriY AlT~awaAriqu biAlHaSaY\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA zaAjiraAtu AlT~ayori maA A@ll~`hu SaAniEu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "By thy life,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by thy religion, the diviners with pebbles know not, nor the diviners by the flight of birds, what God is doing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, O.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "O", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}